(for
you
know
I
cannot
trust
Sarah
to
cook
a
single
dish),
she
sneers.
If
I
accept
an
invitation
out
to
tea,
which
I
have
done
once
or
twice,
I
perceive
I
am
put
quite
into
the
background;
I
have
not
that
attention
paid
me
which
decidedly
