"Do
not
spoil
Caroline,
I
entreat
you,
brother.
Do
not
make
her
of
more
consequence
than
she
ought
to
be.
At
present
she
is
modest
and
unassuming:
let
us
keep
her
so."
"With
all
my
heart.
Is
she
coming
this
morning?"
"She
will
come
at
ten,
as
usual,
to
take
her
French
lesson."
"You
don't
find
that
she
sneers
at
you,
do
you?"
"She
does
not.
She
appreciates
me
better
than
any
one
else
here;
but
then
